Thanks for your comment.  In general, the concept of having a separate mobile site and a "main" site for larger viewing displays is starting to become an older, obsolete concept in the realm of website designers.  Newer developed web sites are being developed using <a href="http://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/website/mobile-devices-responsive-templates-rwd">responsive design</a>.  This allows the user to have a single website that will automatically adapt to the display of the viewer, without using a re-direct.  Google is in essence trying to give precedence those who have made the effort to accommodate the many different devices that can view the web in this day and age.  We do have a few resources about responsive design, but if you do a search, you'll find an exhaustive amount of material that will help to explain the use of responsive web design in the industry today.<br />
